 "components": {
  "instruction": "You are given a text input that represents a user's spoken or written command, request, or query, typically relevant to virtual assistants or smart assistant scenarios. Your goal is to classify this text into one and only one of the following categories:\n\n- alarm_query\n- alarm_set\n- calendar_query\n- calendar_remove\n- calendar_set\n- cooking_recipe\n- datetime_query\n- email_query\n- email_sendemail\n- general_quirky\n- iot_hue_lightoff\n- lists_createoradd\n- lists_query\n- lists_remove\n- music_query\n- news_query\n- play_audiobook\n- play_music\n- play_podcasts\n- play_radio\n- qa_currency\n- qa_definition\n- qa_factoid\n- qa_stock\n- recommendation_events\n- recommendation_locations\n- social_post\n- takeaway_order\n- transport_query\n- weather_query\n\nWhen deciding between similar categories, use the following guidelines based on domain-specific distinctions:\n\n- Use **alarm_set** for instructions related to setting an alarm that will ring at a specified time (e.g., \"Set an alarm for 7 AM\"), typically for waking up or reminders involving a ringing alert.\n- Use **calendar_set** for actions related to creating events or reminders that involve a scheduled entry in a calendar, such as meetings, appointments, or reminders meant to be tracked or displayed on a calendar service (e.g., \"make a reminder for Friday at 6 p.m.\", \"add meeting with Bob at three\").\n- Use **calendar_query** for inquiries about calendar events, and **alarm_query** for inquiries about alarms that have been set.\n- Be attentive to language cues: requests involving \"reminders\" to perform actions at a time or date often belong in **calendar_set**, not **alarm_set**. However, direct phrasing about alarms or waking up should be **alarm_set**.\n- Only output the name of the most appropriate category from the provided list, without any additional justificiation or commentary.\n\nThis is a single-label classification task. Ensure your classification accurately reflects the intent and context of the provided text, considering distinctions between alarms and calendar/reminder entries as described."
 },
